{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1252/comments/3633082.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/gazebo/diff/osrf/gazebo:2b7b77877513..11c5e2317bc7?path=gazebo%2Fgui%2FGuiIface.cc"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1252/_/diff#comment-3633082"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1252, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1252.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1252"}}, "title": "GuiIface reads GAZEBO_GUI_INI_FILE environment variable"}, "content": {"raw": "The structure of this `if` block could be a bit easier to read using:\n\n```\n#!c++\n\nchar *guiINIPath = getenv(\"GAZEBO_GUI_INI_PATH\");\nchar *home = getenv(\"HOME\");\nboost::filesystem::path path;\n\n// The GAZEBO_GUI_INI_PATH takes precedence\nif (guiINIPath)\n{\n  path = guiINIPath;\n}\nelse if (home)\n{\n  path = home;\n  path = path / \".gazebo\" / \"gui.ini\";\n}\n\n// Attempt to read the gui.ini file if the path is not empty\nif (!path.empty())\n{\n  gzmsg << \"Reading gui.ini file from \" << path << std::endl;\n  if (!(result = gui::loadINI(path)))\n  {\n    gzerr << \"Unable to read gui.ini from\" << path << std::endl;\n  }\n}\nelse\n{\n  gzerr << \"HOME and GAZEBO_GUI_INI_PATH environment variables not found. Unable to read gui.ini file.\\n\";\n  result = false;\n}\n```\n", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>The structure of this <code>if</code> block could be a bit easier to read using:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-c++\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"kt\">char</span> <span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">guiINIPath</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">getenv</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">&quot;GAZEBO_GUI_INI_PATH&quot;</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"kt\">char</span> <span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">home</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\"